    <section>
        <h2>Question 1: What is microbiology?</h2>
        <p>Microbiology is the study of microorganisms, which include bacteria, viruses, fungi, and protozoa.</p>

        <h2>Question 2: What are the main types of microorganisms?</h2>
        <p>The main types of microorganisms are bacteria, viruses, fungi, and algae.</p>

        <h2>Question 3: What is the role of bacteria in the ecosystem?</h2>
        <p>Bacteria play crucial roles in nutrient cycling, such as decomposing organic matter and fixing nitrogen.</p>
